# Tri-Platform UI Sync (Web + Mobile Customer + Mobile Cook)

Singapore Home Cooks has **three client surfaces** that must look and behave as one product:

| Surface | Path |
|---------|------|
| Web | `apps/web/` |
| Mobile Customer | `apps/mobile-customer/` |
| Mobile Cook | `apps/mobile-cook/` |
| Shared tokens/components | `packages/shc-ui/` |
| Brand source of truth | `brand.md` |

## Mandatory on every UI/brand change

When you change colors, typography, spacing, shadows, borders, component APIs, or screen layout patterns:

1. **Read `brand.md` first** — Neo-Brutalist Food UI + Bento design system
2. **Update tokens in all token files:**
   - `packages/shc-ui/src/theme.ts`
   - `apps/web/app/globals.css` (`--shc-*` aliases)
3. **Update shared components:**
   - Mobile: `packages/shc-ui/src/primitives.tsx`, `domain.tsx`
   - Web: `apps/web/app/components/SHCWebComponents.tsx`
4. **Update screens** on every platform affected by the change (do not ship web-only or mobile-only visual updates)
5. **Update `brand.md`** if palette, patterns, or voice change
6. **Update blueprint:** `blueprint/12-shared-components/12-shared-components.md` + `CURRENT_STATE.md` if integration status changes
7. **Preserve Maestro `testID`s** — run `bash scripts/run-maestro-full-tour.sh` after layout refactors

## Forbidden

- Hardcoding old jade green `#1D9E75` or any hex not in `shcColors` / CSS variables
- Updating only `apps/web` while leaving `@shc/ui` on stale tokens
- Adding screen-level inline colors instead of `@shc/ui` tokens (mobile) or CSS variables (web)

## Why mobile looked "old"

Mobile consumed `@shc/ui` with legacy jade tokens while web used Peach Comfort / Neo-Brutalist `globals.css`. This rule prevents that drift.

